feat(setup): one-command bootstrap, doctor diagnostics, and first-run flow

Setup automation
- npm run bootstrap: cross-platform wrapper that picks bootstrap.ps1
  on Windows or bootstrap.sh on macOS/Linux. Verifies Node version,
  installs all workspaces, links the CLI globally, and runs doctor.
- npm run doctor: validates Node version, workspace shape, installed
  deps, OS-specific DB path + writability, CLI link presence, and port
  availability. Exits non-zero with OS-specific fix hints (e.g.
  Get-NetTCPConnection on Windows, lsof on Unix).
- npm run db:where / db:reset: surface the actual SQLite location
  (%APPDATA%, ~/.config, ~/Library) and offer a confirmed wipe with
  WAL/SHM sidecar cleanup; --yes flag for non-interactive use.

First-run experience
- When `habit` runs against an empty DB in a TTY, offer an interactive
  starter prompt with three suggestions (Code 1 hour, Drink 2L water,
  Read 30 minutes), a custom-name option, or skip. Falls back to the
  static empty-state for non-TTY contexts.

Quality of life
- npm run dev now uses `concurrently -n api,web -c cyan,magenta` for
  prefixed, color-coded logs.
- New `npm run check`: lint + production build in one shot.
- Root package.json declared `type: module` to silence Node's typeless
  package warning when running scripts/.

Docs
- README: bootstrap step replaces manual setup; new "Maintenance
  commands" table.
- CHEATSHEET: corrected the DB reset path (was wrongly pointing at
  backend/data/, the real location is in the OS config dir);
  troubleshooting section now uses the new npm scripts.
